<HEADLINE>
<P>
ENGAGEMENTS; 
</P>
<P>
MCDERMOTT-BRITTINGHAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mr. and Mrs. Franklin Otis Booth Jr. of Bel-Air hosted a family party to 
announce the betrothal of her daughter, Ashley Cummins Brittingham, to Jeffrey 
Alan McDermott. 
</P>
<P>
The bride-elect, a graduate of Marlborough School and of Southern Methodist 
University, is a member of Kappa Alpha Theta and of the Spinsters, Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
Her father is the late Thomas Evans Brittingham. 
</P>
<P>
Her stepfather, a private investor/rancher, served as group vice president of 
Times Mirror Co. and as chairman of Publisher's Paper Co. He is the great 
grandson of Gen. Harrison Gray Otis, founder of Times Mirror Co., the parent 
company of the Los Angeles Times. 
</P>
<P>
The bridegroom-to-be, a vice president of Merrill Lynch Capital Markets in 
Westwood, is a graduate of UC Berkeley where he was affiliated with Phi Gamma 
Delta; he also received a master's degree from the UCLA School of Business. 
</P>
<P>
McDermott's parents are William John McDermott of Los Altos Hills, founder and 
retired chief executive officer of Pacific Computer Corp., and Mrs. Cleary 
McDermott of Los Altos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Ashley Cummins Brittingham 
</P>
