</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Authorities are investigating the cause of a fire that swept through the Big 
Oaks Lodge, causing $150,000 in damage to the century-old restaurant northeast 
of Saugus, authorities said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
The fire began about 4 a.m. Saturday and burned the restaurant, bar and kitchen 
of the two-story lodge at 33100 Bouquet Canyon Road in an isolated, woodsy area 
monitored by the U.S. Forest Service, Los Angeles County Fire Department 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
No one was in the dining areas, and the lodge's cabins and a training facility 
for boxers escaped the flames, Capt. Terry Holden said. 
</P>
