<P>
OPEC Earnings Jump: The oil revenue of the OPEC nations soared last year to 
their highest level since 1985, an industry analyst said. Pierre Terzian, 
editor of the Paris-based newsletter Petrostrategies, estimated that the 
13-nation Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries earned a combined total 
of $110.6 billion last year from export sales of their crude, up more than a 
third from his 1988 calculation of $80.1 billion. 
