<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
PHILIPPINES; 
</P>
<P>
TROOPS CAPTURE RENEGADE GENERAL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Philippine troops in a dawn raid today captured a rebel general regarded as one 
of the main organizers of last month's failed coup against President Corazon 
Aquino, the military said. Brig. Gen. Edgardo Abenina, who had a $44,500 price 
on his head, is the most senior officer arrested since the rebellion was 
crushed. Military officials said he suffered bruises trying to escape troops 
who surrounded his Manila hide-out. 
</P>
