<HEADLINE>
<P>
BERGER REPLACES KRICKSTEIN ON DAVIS CUP TEAM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By THOMAS BONK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jay Berger was selected Sunday to replace injured Aaron Krickstein in next 
weekend's first-round Davis Cup match between the United States and Mexico at 
La Costa. 
</P>
<P>
Berger, ranked No. 9 in the world, and No. 4 Brad Gilbert will be the U.S. 
singles players. Gilbert was also a substitute. He replaced Michael Chang, who 
separated a bone in his hip in December. 
</P>
<P>
U.S. Davis Cup captain Tom Gorman said he contacted Berger after Krickstein 
pulled a groin muscle in the Australian Open 10 days ago. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm glad he was available on such short notice," Gorman said. 
</P>
<P>
Berger's other Davis Cup experience was in 1988, when he won his match in a 3-0 
victory over Peru. THOMAS BONK 
</P>
