<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE; 
</P>
<P>
REGION TRANSPORT BODY PLANNED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Service Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an effort to reduce "bureaucratic gridlock," Southern California lawmakers 
announced plans today to form a regional transportation authority for their 
districts. 
</P>
<P>
The new authority would be required to come up with a regional transportation 
plan for the area. It also would have the final say -- and resolve differences 
between cities and counties -- on all transportation issues in the counties of 
Los Angeles, Orange, Riverside, San Bernardino, Ventura and Imperial. 
</P>
<P>
The plan is expected to draw fierce opposition from the Los Angeles County 
Transportation Commission, which would lose power, and from Orange County, 
which has traditionally opposed having to take orders from a regional 
authority. 
</P>
</TEXT>
