<P>
COLGATE BUYS CANADIAN FIRMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Colgate-Palmolive Co. today announced an agreement to acquire Canada's bleach 
and fabric softener businesses from Bristol Myers Squibb Co. for $172 million. 
</P>
<P>
The purchase is part of Colgate's strategy to be a major force in the 
profitable bleach category, said Reuben Mark, the consumer products company's 
chairman, president and chief executive officer. 
</P>
<P>
Before buying the two businesses, which will be known as the Javex 
Manufacturing Co. Inc. and the Javex Marketing Co. Inc., Colgate was the 
largest marketer of household bleach outside North America, Mark said. 
</P>
<P>
Colgate built a strong presence in bleach overseas mainly through its 
acquisition of the Cotelle and Klorin bleach businesses in Europe and by 
introducing its own brands in selected world markets. 
</P>
<P>
The addition of the Javex companies will almost double Colgate's revenue base 
in Canada. 
</P>
