<P>
LATINOVISION: Before launching Orange County's only local Spanish-language TV 
service (B1), KBUENAvision asked Latinos in Santa Ana what they'd like to see. 
. . . It turns out they want what everyone else wants: More than half want 
movies, nearly half want sports, about a third want telenovelas (soap operas) 
and only about 10% want news. "When you survey special groups, there's almost 
never a significant difference," said the cable channel's Doug Montandon. . . . 
In sports, however, Latinos want soccer and boxing. Mark I. Pinsky and Steve 
Emmons 
