<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 3; Column 5; Metro Desk 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
136 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FULLERTON; 
</P>
<P>
GROUP PLANS SUIT ON PETITION'S LANGUAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A residents' group seeking to control traffic noise through a ballot initiative 
has decided to delay circulating a petition on the measure and to file suit to 
change the wording of the petition's summary instead. 
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, Save Our Bastanchury vowed to gather enough signatures to 
call a special election and place its measure before voters. 
</P>
<P>
The city attorney's summary of that measure, released Wednesday, must appear at 
the top of each petition. 
</P>
<P>
But Mary Homme, president of Save Our Bastanchury, said members considered that 
summary biased and inaccurate. The group unanimously decided to file suit in 
Superior Court in about two weeks to force the city to write a better summary, 
she said. 
</P>
<P>
City Atty. R. K. (Kerry) Fox, said he believed his summary is accurate and 
unbiased. TOM McQUEENEY 
</P>
</TEXT>
