<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOPEZ FACES GONZALEZ IN TITLE FIGHT AT IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
IRVINE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ben Lopez faces Vicente Gonzalez for the vacant state super featherweight title 
tonight in the main event of the monthly boxing program at the Irvine Marriott 
Hotel. 
</P>
<P>
Lopez, of Ontario, has a record of 14-4 and won his last bout in Irvine with a 
second-round knockout of Armando Barez. Gonzalez, of Los Angeles, is 15-5. This 
the first time he has fought at Irvine. 
</P>
<P>
The first of five scheduled bouts starts at 7:30 p.m. Tickets go on sale at 10 
a.m. in the hotel ballroom. 
